node.title: NT records one new COVID case but lockout to end in Greater DarwinÂ
node.alt: A man wearing a face mask walks in front of a shop window in the Smith St Mall in Darwin's CBD.
node.description: The Northern Territory has recorded one new case of COVID-19, Chief Minister Michael Gunner says.
node.content: ["The Greater Darwin lockout will end at midnight tonight, Chief Minister Michael Gunner says, despite the\u00a0Northern Territory\u00a0recording\u00a0one new case of COVID-19.", "Mr Gunner said the positive case was\u00a0a household contact of the first case\u00a0detected in the outbreak\u00a0last week.", "He entered\u00a0Howard Springs on\u00a0November 5 and has\u00a0been in isolation for his entire infectious period, Mr Gunner said.", "He initially\u00a0tested\u00a0negative on arrival at Howard Springs and his second test also came back negative.", "The new case was not a threat to the community and there were no new close contacts or exposure sites linked to the case, Mr Gunner said.", "The\u00a0case brings the total number of reported infections in the current outbreak to four.", "A mask mandate will remain in place in Greater Darwin until 5pm on Friday.", "Yesterday Mr Gunner announced the\u00a0lockout for Greater Darwin, which was due to originally lift at midnight on Sunday, would be extended by\u00a024 hours for a second time.", "A lockout in\u00a0Katherine ended yesterday at 5pm.", "More to come."]
